  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want messages to show up in an intuitive order so I can have a familiar and pleasant user experience.\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to understand and communicate semantics of message ordering clock-value.\r\n\r\nAs a (dev)tester, I want to report bugs that are bugs and not expected behavior.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature/Spike\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Spike out mini buffer where messages aren't acked (received) and this is ideally visually represented.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nRe-order messages when they arrive in wrong order in short timespan and visually distinguish this.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIt can appear as if messages are \"in wrong order\" https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/2699 even though this is the correct semantics.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nFrom Slack:\r\nTLDR if you receive message 3 first it is _received_ first. If you later, even 10ms later, get message 1 and 2 then you need to choose: do we update ordering based on information (change UI) or so we append? This is a design decision and we default to latter right now.\r\n\r\nEvent chain:\r\n```\r\nSEND 1\r\nSEND 2\r\nSEND 3\r\n<indeterministic network>\r\nRECV 3  - received first so committed first\r\nRECV 2 - we know senders clock-value so we can choose to re-order based on this info (and careful reasoning so we preserve Lamport semantics, for example tempids/uncommitted messages)\r\nRECV 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso investigate if this problem is reproducible, in which it case the behavior on _send_ side might be \"wrong\"/suboptimal. I.e. SEND 1 2 3 on client results in Whisper \"publish\" 3 2 1 due to faulty buffer or something.\r\n\r\nAlso think carefully about implications for group chat. Probably need short circuit when sending messages to preserve Lamport semantics.\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n- Initial PR https://github.com/status-im/status-react/commit/db6b80d529f3b7512d4831b88246b60a86072b1f\r\n- Relevant ns: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/db6b80d529f3b7512d4831b88246b60a86072b1f/src/status_im/utils/clocks.cljs\r\n- Relevant tests for invariants preserved: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/test/cljs/status_im/test/utils/clocks.cljs",
